====================================================
Titan Phase‑6 — End‑of‑Session Summary
Date: 2025‑11‑18
Precision Mode: ON
====================================================

Topics and Summaries:

- Hybrid Memory Architecture:
  - Evaluated three approaches: single file, fully modular, and hybrid.
  - Pros and cons of each approach discussed.
  - Decided on hybrid: one master JSON file + linked modules (boot, user, identity, history, runtime).
  - Hybrid preserves clarity, scalability, token efficiency, and mobile compatibility.

- Memory Implementation Goals:
  - Stable long-term memory persisted in GitHub.
  - Structured knowledge management and reduced hallucination.
  - Automatic context reconstruction at “Hello Titan” and summary storage at “Goodbye.”

- Implementation Plan:
  - Master JSON file points to linked modules.
  - Loader script reads master, fetches modules, injects memory into Titan.
  - Session-end summary appended to history module.
  - Python loader commits updates to GitHub automatically.

- Required Software (All Free):
  - Pydroid 3 (Android Python environment) to run loader.
  - GitHub Android app for managing memory files.
  - Text editor (Acode or QuickEdit) optional for manual JSON edits.
  - GitHub Personal Access Token for authenticated read/write.

- Memory Implementation Philosophy File:
  - Persistent record stored at: https://github.com/nicolaskritzinger/Titan-boot-files/edit/main/Memory_implementaion_philosophy
  - All future architecture updates to be documented there.

====================================================
